  system-config-display-1.0.51.ebuild:
  I said, 'remove xsri dep.'

*system-config-display-1.0.51 (15 Jul 2007)

  15 Jul 2007; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  +system-config-display-1.0.51.ebuild:
  Bump. Fail gracefully on non-graphical systems, allow for xorg.conf to be a
  symlink, start X with black background to remove xsri dep, load mouse/kbd
  setup from config file instead of clobbering them.

*system-config-display-1.0.45 (22 Sep 2006)

  22 Sep 2006; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  -system-config-display-1.0.44.ebuild,
  +system-config-display-1.0.45.ebuild:
  Bump. Refresh the mode state before first paint, to give rhpxl a chance to
  ask RANDR for the current mode.

  06 Sep 2006; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  system-config-display-1.0.44.ebuild:
  Add note that people may need to reinstall video drivers for autodetection.

  05 Sep 2006; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  system-config-display-1.0.44.ebuild:
  Cleanup compiled python files.

*system-config-display-1.0.44 (05 Sep 2006)

  05 Sep 2006; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>; +metadata.xml,
  +system-config-display-1.0.44.ebuild:
